 </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":3,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":0} -->
<p class="heading_excerpt">An AUR helper like yay lets you download and install packages from the Arch User Repository. Here's how to install yay on Arch Linux.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":4,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":133} --><div class="heading_image responsive-img img-size-heading-image-full-width expandable " style="padding-bottom:50%" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg" data-modal-id="single-image-modal" data-modal-container-id="single-image-modal-container" data-img-caption="&quot;&quot;">
 
<figure> <picture> <!--[if IE 9]> <video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="1140px" srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg?q=50&fit=contain&w=1140&h=&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg?q=50&fit=contain&w=943&h=&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg?q=50&fit=contain&w=767&h=&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg?q=50&fit=contain&w=480&h=&dpr=1.5"/> <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img width="1680" height="840" alt="installing yay on arch linux" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/installing-yay-on-arch-linux.jpg"/> </picture> <figcaption class="item-img-caption"></figcaption> </figure> </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":5,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":133} -->
 <!-- No winning ad found for zone: below main pic! --> </header>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":6,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":133} --><section id="article-body" class="article-body" itemprop="articleBody"><div class="affiliate-sponsored">
 
<span data-nosnippet>Readers like you help support MUO. When you make a purchase using links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission. <a href="/page/terms-of-use">Read more.</a></span></div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":7,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":133} -->
<p>Pacman is a powerful package manager that ships as the default on Arch-based distros, but it lacks the functionality of downloading packages from the Arch User Repository (AUR). The AUR is a community-maintained repository providing thousands of third-party packages in the form of installation scripts, also known as PKGBUILDs.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":0,"nbrPlacementsScanned":8,"ruleCount":650,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":461} -->
 <!-- No winning ad found for zone: below first paragraph! --><!-- No winning ad found for zone: mid intro! --> 
<p>To install packages using these PKGBUILDs, we require an AUR helper like yay. yay doesn&#39;t come preinstalled on Arch Linux and isn&#39;t available in the official Arch repositories either. So how do you install yay to download packages from the AUR on your Arch desktop? Let&#39;s find out.</p>
<!-- Zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- No ads allowed! -->
 <!-- No winning ad found for zone: native in content! -->
<h2 id="how-to-install-yay-on-arch-linux"> How to Install yay on Arch Linux</h2>
<p>The yay package is only available in the Arch User Repository. Note that you can manually install packages from the AUR without using an AUR helper (similar to how we&#39;ll install yay below), but as the name suggests, an &quot;AUR helper&quot; assists you in the installation process, making it easier for you to install packages with minimum user interaction.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":10,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":362} -->
<p>To install yay on your Arch desktop, first, download the following dependencies:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":11,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":442} -->
<code class="hljs sql">sudo pacman -S <span class="hljs-comment">--needed base-devel git</span></code>
<p>Then, clone the yay repository <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/clone-github-repository-git-bash/">using the git clone command</a>:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":12,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":501} -->
<code class="hljs php">git <span class="hljs-keyword">clone</span> https:<span class="hljs-comment">//aur.archlinux.org/yay.git</span></code>
<p>Change your present working directory to the newly-downloaded <strong>yay</strong> folder using <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/cd-command-in-linux/">the cd command</a>:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":13,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":595} -->
<code class="hljs bash"><span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> yay</code>
<p>Finally, use the makepkg command to build and install yay:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":14,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":653} -->
<code class="hljs ">makepkg -si</code>
<p>If the above command throws the &quot;cannot find the fakeroot binary&quot; error, make sure you&#39;ve successfully installed the <strong>base-devel</strong> package and then re-run the command.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":15,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":831} -->
<section class="emaki-custom-block emaki-custom-note"><div class="emaki-custom note" id="custom_block_13"><p>In addition to Arch Linux, this method works for <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/best-arch-based-linux-distros/">other Arch-based distributions</a> as well, including Manjaro, EndeavourOS, and Garuda Linux.</p> </div></section>
<p>Once done, verify the installation by checking the version of yay installed.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":16,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":907} -->
<code class="hljs sql">yay <span class="hljs-comment">--version</span></code>
<p>If the output returns a version number, you have succeeded in installing yay.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":1,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":17,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":984} -->
<p>The AUR isn&#39;t originally built for use on Linux distros other than Arch Linux and its derivatives (like Ubuntu and Linux Mint). On such distributions, you can use <a href="https://github.com/pacstall/pacstall" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Pacstall</a>, an AUR-inspired package manager that provides pacscripts for installing software.</p>
<!-- Zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- No ads allowed! --><div class=ad-odd>
<!-- No winning ad found for zone: every images #1! --></div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":19,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":0} -->
<h2 id="how-to-manage-aur-packages-using-yay"> How to Manage AUR Packages Using yay</h2>
<p>yay and Pacman commands have a lot in common. For example, to install a new package using Pacman or yay, you use the <strong>-S</strong> flag, whereas to remove one, you&#39;ve to use the <strong>-R</strong> option.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":20,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":181} -->
<p>Now that you know the similarity between the two package managers, let&#39;s begin with <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/how-to-install-and-remove-packages-arch-linux/">package management on Arch Linux</a> using yay.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":21,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":312} -->
<h3 id="searching-for-aur-packages">Searching for AUR Packages</h3>
<p>Like Pacman, yay allows users to search for packages prior to installing them. If you&#39;re unsure about the name of a particular package, you can use the yay command with the search term to find related packages.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":22,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":526} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay searchterm</code>
<p>For example, to search for packages with &quot;chrome&quot; in their name:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":23,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":600} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay chrome</code>
<p>Output:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":24,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":607} --><div class="body-img landscape"><div class="responsive-img image-expandable img-article-item" style="padding-bottom:63.542642924086%" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg" data-modal-id="single-image-modal" data-modal-container-id="single-image-modal-container" data-img-caption="&quot;&quot;">
 
<figure> <picture> <!--[if IE 9]> <video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="1500px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=1500&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=943&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=767&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=480&dpr=1.5"/> <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img width="1067" height="678" class="lazyload" alt="searching packages with yay" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/searching-packages-with-yay.jpg"/> </picture> </figure> </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":25,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":607} -->
 </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":26,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":607} -->
<p>To search for a package on both the official repositories and the AUR, use the <strong>-Ss</strong> flag:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":27,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":695} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Ss google-chrome</code>
<p>You can also specify multiple keywords to perform a narrow, more focused search as follows:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":28,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":786} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -S term1 term2</code>
<p>The aforementioned command will first search for <strong>term1</strong> and then narrow down the results by searching for <strong>term2</strong> in the returned results.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":29,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":921} -->
<h3 id="installing-packages-with-yay">Installing Packages With yay</h3>
<p>As discussed before, to install packages with yay, simply specify the package name next to the <strong>-S</strong> flag:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":2,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":2,"nbrPlacementsScanned":30,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":1024} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -S packagename</code>
<p>To install the Google Chrome AUR package using yay:</p>
<!-- Zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- No ads allowed! -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -S google-chrome</code>
<section class="emaki-custom-block emaki-custom-note"><div class="emaki-custom note" id="custom_block_38"><p>The installation process isn&#39;t completely automatic and you might have to enter your superuser password in the middle of the installation.</p> </div></section>
<p>To only get the PKGBUILD of a package, use the <strong>-G</strong> or <strong>--getpkgbuild</strong> flag:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":32,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":72} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -G google-chrome</code>
<p>You can also choose to print the PKGBUILD by using the <strong>-p</strong> flag with <strong>-G</strong>:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":33,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":143} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Gp google-chrome</code>
<p>Output:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":34,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":150} --><div class="body-img landscape"><div class="responsive-img image-expandable img-article-item" style="padding-bottom:47.981366459627%" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg" data-modal-id="single-image-modal" data-modal-container-id="single-image-modal-container" data-img-caption="&quot;&quot;">
 
<figure> <picture> <!--[if IE 9]> <video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="1500px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=1500&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=943&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=767&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=480&dpr=1.5"/> <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img width="1288" height="618" class="lazyload" alt="view pkgbuild with yay" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/view-pkgbuild-with-yay.jpg"/> </picture> </figure> </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":35,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":150} -->
 </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":36,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":150} -->
<h3 id="removing-packages-with-yay">Removing Packages With yay</h3>
<p>When you don&#39;t need an AUR package and want to remove it from your system, use the <strong>-R</strong> option:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":37,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":247} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -R packagename</code>
<p>To uninstall Google Chrome:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":38,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":274} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -R google-chrome</code>
<p>If you want to remove the dependencies along with the package, append the <strong>-ns</strong> flag to the previous command:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":39,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":381} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Rns google-chrome</code>
<h3 id="upgrading-aur-packages">Upgrading AUR Packages</h3>
<p>Invoking the yay command without any arguments will perform a full system upgrade similar to the <strong>pacman -Syu</strong> command. Note that this command will also synchronize and upgrade packages from the official repositories in addition to the AUR.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":40,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":619} -->
<p>To only update AUR packages, use the <strong>-Sua</strong> flag with the command:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":41,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":683} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Sua</code>
<p>If you <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/prevent-packages-from-getting-updated-arch-linux/">don&#39;t want to update a package on Arch Linux</a>, you&#39;ll have to modify the configuration file located at <strong>/etc/pacman.conf</strong>. Linux also allows you to <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/how-to-downgrade-packages-linux/">downgrade packages on your system</a> if you want.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":3,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":3,"nbrPlacementsScanned":42,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":889} -->
<h3 id="using-yay-to-remove-unnecessary-dependencies">Using yay to Remove Unnecessary Dependencies</h3>
<p>Unused dependencies can quickly pile up and consume a huge chunk of your system storage if not taken care of. You can either choose to remove the dependencies along with the packages by using the <strong>-Rns</strong> flag each time you remove something, or you can take the better route by sweeping them away all at once using the <strong>-Yc</strong> flag.</p>
<!-- Zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- No ads allowed! -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Yc</code>
<p>The <strong>-Y</strong> in the command stands for &quot;yay&quot; and will only perform operations on packages installed using yay.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":44,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":114} -->
<h3 id="additional-yay-commands">Additional yay Commands</h3>
<p>To print package statistics and system health with yay, run the following command:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":45,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":196} -->
<code class="hljs ">yay -Ps</code>
<p>Output:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":46,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":203} --><div class="body-img landscape"><div class="responsive-img image-expandable img-article-item" style="padding-bottom:63.756906077348%" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg" data-modal-id="single-image-modal" data-modal-container-id="single-image-modal-container" data-img-caption="&quot;&quot;">
 
<figure> <picture> <!--[if IE 9]> <video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="1500px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=1500&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=943&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=767&dpr=1.5"/> <source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=480&dpr=1.5"/> <!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img width="905" height="577" class="lazyload" alt="print statistics using yay" data-img-url="https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/print-statistics-using-yay.jpg"/> </picture> </figure> </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":47,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":203} -->
 </div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":48,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":203} -->
<p>In case you need help with the commands, you can <a href="https://www.makeuseof.com/command-line-help-linux/">easily get command-line help</a> using the <strong>--help</strong> flag:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":49,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":303} -->
<code class="hljs sql">yay <span class="hljs-comment">--help</span></code>
<p>Alternatively, you can view the yay manual page using:</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":50,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":357} -->
<code class="hljs ">man yay</code><div class=ad-even>
<!-- No winning ad found for zone: every images #2! --></div>

<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":51,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":357} -->
<h2 id="the-aur-has-got-everything-you-need"> The AUR Has Got Everything You Need!</h2>
<p>Now that installing AUR packages is a breeze for you, go check out the AUR and search for software that you&#39;ve always wanted to install on Linux. There&#39;s a good chance that it&#39;ll be available in the repository.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":52,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":579} -->
<p>Keep in mind that using the AUR also poses a security risk. Since anyone can add their PKGBUILD to the AUR, these installation scripts aren&#39;t often tested and reviewed properly. But that doesn&#39;t mean you should stop downloading packages from the AUR altogether.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":53,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":848} -->
<p>Instead, minimize the risk by reviewing the PKGBUILDs before installing the packages. Not only will this keep your system safe, but you&#39;ll also learn how packages in the AUR work.</p>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":54,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":1031} -->
<div id="article-waypoint"></div>
<!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. --><!-- Repeatable debug data: {"adPosition":4,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":55,"ruleCount":1050,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"actualCount":1031} --></section>

